    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "bf6105ca7bfd4f6b9603b37ea2d3bbb4",
      "x": 22985.53183120697,
      "y": -455.898577055822,
      "width": 422.0745171302942,
      "height": 301.88674083086244,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Each Claude response node now picks a random emoji on creation (persisted in the data so it survives save/load), and paints it in the same top-left position as WarmNode's accent. Existing sessions without the field will get a fresh random pick on first load.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#8a7a67"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Omnious",
      "uuid": "1fded24b84584ca3bec6de3b27e09324",
      "x": 15304.543667843664,
      "y": 7160.3634826960315,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 312.0,
      "z_value": -9.934000000000037,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "This is Basalt\nSay hello to Basalt everyone\nBasalt is special\n\nIt\u00b4s a bit stiff when it gets here\nSo we need to be kind to it\n\nIt gets totally crushed\n\nHow do we measure\nAggression versus compassion\n\nTime, becoming the gardeners ally\nWithin our tapestry of shared success"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Thank You",
      "uuid": "8db0fd7a21804c70acae62a4f8f745b3",
      "x": 14774.812948196417,
      "y": 5186.239816359066,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 344.0,
      "z_value": -9.930000000000039,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "First of all thank you.  \n\nBut mostly because it is important for us to remember \nThat in this world a human being saw some chickens \n\nAnd thought, hey! \nWhy is our world so amazing \nAnd their world so dirty and dark. \n\nAnd then went ahead and invented virtual reality goggles\nThat fit snuggly on the heads of chickens \nSo they run around on paradisic fields all day \nIn absolute joy and bliss as advertised on TV."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "914ecddea6964223b9b9a7aa556b477e",
      "x": 17771.457426087713,
      "y": 923.8818973399202,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 344.0,
      "z_value": -9.889000000000062,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The root cause fix: `to_dict()` no longer calls `_encode_to_b64()` for file-backed images \u2014 the data layer was already discarding the b64 for those, so the encode was pure wasted QPainter work. The suppression list catches any residual cases (e.g. paste-only images serialized before the render context is fully warm).",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Look!",
      "uuid": "a65cecf92e974bdf9c3112043bce2b75",
      "x": 8760.61906372397,
      "y": 6969.2464788011175,
      "width": 304.5752017114978,
      "height": 152.0,
      "z_value": -9.94500000000003,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "During this walk home they met some men\nWho began prying into their affairs.\nStarted shouting look! look! look at that little boy!\nLeaving a poor old man tired walking behind"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "sequence",
      "title": "New folder",
      "uuid": "07fbcca4360e4c1787ff013cc07b6a55",
      "x": 14719.69064710454,
      "y": 4289.375914243612,
      "width": 320.0,
      "height": 300.0,
      "z_value": -9.726000000000152,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "folder_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\The Dawn of a new Era of Mankind\\Original Page Text\\03\\New folder",
      "current_frame": 0
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "67c2e6905c9c434194fe1bc601e674dd",
      "x": 23330.639745343367,
      "y": 3115.3269041179774,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The pattern is clear now \u2014 every time Qt does something that disturbs the view/scene widget lifecycle (hide/show of the central widget, geometry resize during animation) there's a window where the scene's mouse state goes stale. The curtains restore is the third distinct trigger, so the right fix is a single shared cleanup that runs at the end of every curtains animation rather than patching each scenario individually.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#9a4a4a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Soft",
      "uuid": "27f013b0b52a424289068da96195807a",
      "x": 1965.3322776386804,
      "y": -871.7109871840636,
      "width": 60.68859111207803,
      "height": 28.01179865280983,
      "z_value": -9.978000000000012,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Soft",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "cc0503425b844302898ed79464edfa88",
      "x": 19848.956028453562,
      "y": 2427.282556981877,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Found it. In `BaseNode.__init__`, `NodeBehaviour` is created at line 120, then `setBrush(Theme.nodeBg)` at line 133. `AboutNode` then overrides with `setBrush(self._bg_color())`. That part is fine. The bug is: when the shuffle button is clicked while hovering, `bg_anim` is still running with its old end value \u2014 it fires `_on_bg_changed` after `_apply_depth` sets the new brush, overwriting it. We need to stop the animation before resetting:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#9a4a4a"
    },
